  "acceptance_criteria": [
    "Replace the player-visible prototype dashboard framing with a Beta app shell containing top status, central map region, side inspector area, objective/action area, settings/language entry, and explicit dev overlay separation.",
    "Player mode must not show prototype text, milestone labels, state hashes, revisions, raw reason codes, raw IDs, or test-only names by default.",
    "All player-visible app-shell strings use the accepted i18n foundation and work in English, Simplified Chinese, and system fallback.",
    "The shell remains a presentation/read-model coordinator and does not own authoritative WorldState, submit hidden commands, or duplicate simulation formulas.",
    "Storybook and Playwright coverage demonstrate normal, empty, error, narrow, English, Simplified Chinese, and debug-on/off states without incoherent overlap.",
    "No release/commercial/branding decision, production art, telemetry, server, multiplayer, account, cloud save, or manual node battle scope is introduced."
  ],
